The paper deals with the problem of generating natural language descriptions of videos, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed architecture involves deep learning techniques such as Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) and Recurrent Neural Networks (RNN), which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. The incorporation of semantic attributes from images and videos also suggests a potential connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and knowledge representation.
